The paper deals with a data structure problem involving range queries in 2D, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of effective entropy and succinct indices suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The problem of range maxima queries also has connections to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.CC).
